  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to keep the current chat conversation position after opening URLs with the build-in browser so that I would be able to keep track of the current context the URL was posted in. \r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*:  The chat window scrolls down to the end of a conversation when opening a URL with the build-in browser. This might not be convenient in some cases when the end-users need to keep track of the conversation context when the URL was posted.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nTo keep the current chat position after closing the browser window as it is when using an external browser app. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\n\r\nThe chat window scrolls down to the bottom. \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n1. Open Status\r\n2. Open 1-1 or group chat\r\n3. Enter or find an URL somewhere in the beginning/middle of a long conversation so it's not longer visible on the chat window\r\n4. Scroll up to the URL and click on it\r\n5. Select \"Open in browser\"\r\n6. Close the browser\r\n\r\nRecording: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H5RetIRWk18\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n[comment]: # (Please summarise the solution and provide a task list on what needs to be fixed.)\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\n- Keep the current chat position\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: \r\n\r\nAndroid - 0.9.19 (6034)\r\niOS - 0.9.19 (6031)\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Android or iOS.)\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\n\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/H5RetIRWk18/maxresdefault.jpg\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><img src=\"/yts/img/favicon_144-vfliLAfaB.png\" height=\"14\"> YouTube</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H5RetIRWk18\">Screenrecorder 2018 06 17 20 06 47 0</a></strong></div><div> </div></blockquote>",
